### Step 5: The GitHub Actions YAML 
This file tells GitHub to wake up and run `bot.js` every 5 minutes. 
Create a file at this exact path in your repo: `.github/workflows/bot.yml`


http://googleusercontent.com/immersive_entry_chip/1

---

### Step 6: The True Real-Time Viewer App (Frontend)
Your viewers will load this HTML file. Notice that there is **no `setInterval`** fetching data. It uses Firebase `onSnapshot`. If the GitHub Action writes a profit to the database at exactly 2:05 PM, this webpage will visually update itself at 2:05 PM without the user ever clicking refresh.

(Remember to replace the `firebaseConfig` block with the public config block you get from your Firebase Project Settings -> General -> "Web App").


http://googleusercontent.com/immersive_entry_chip/2

Once you push these files to your GitHub repository, go to the **Actions** tab on GitHub. You will see your "ScalpScanner Engine" workflow listed there. It will start running automatically every 5 minutes forever, totally separated from your computer.
